    • Method Detail

      • getMetamethod

        public static Object getMetamethod(ByteString event,
                                   LuaObject o)
        Returns the entry with the key event of the metatable of the LuaObject o. If o does not have a metatable or event does not exist in it as a key, returns null.

        The access of the metatable is raw (i.e. uses Table.rawget(Object)).

        This method differs from getMetamethod(MetatableProvider, ByteString, Object) in that it does not require a metatable provider as the object in question is known to have metatables attached on a per-instance basis.

        Parameters:
        event - the key to look up in the metatable, must not be null
        o - the object in question, must not be null
        Returns:
        a non-null value if event is a key in o's metatable; null otherwise
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if o or event is null

      • getMetamethod

        public static Object getMetamethod(MetatableProvider metatableProvider,
                                   ByteString event,
                                   Object o)
        Returns the entry with the key event of the metatable of the object o. If o does not have a metatable or event does not exist in it as a key, returns null.

        The access of the metatable is raw (i.e. uses Table.rawget(Object)).

        Parameters:
        metatableProvider - the metatable provider, must not be null
        event - the key to look up in the metatable, must not be null
        o - the object in question, may be null
        Returns:
        a non-null value if event is a key in o's metatable; null otherwise
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if metatableProvider or event is null

      • binaryHandlerFor

        public static Object binaryHandlerFor(MetatableProvider metatableProvider,
                                      ByteString event,
                                      Object a,
                                      Object b)
        Returns the metatable entry event for a or in b, or null if neither a nor b has such an entry in their metatable.

        This method is similar to getMetamethod(MetatableProvider, ByteString, Object), but first looks up the entry event in a, and if this fails (by returning null), tries to look event up in b.

        Parameters:
        metatableProvider - the metatable provider, must not be null
        event - the key to look up in the metatable, must not be null
        a - the first object to try, may be null
        b - the second object to try, may be null
        Returns:
        a non-null value if event is a key in a's or b's metatable (in this order); null otherwise
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if metatableProvider or event is null
